THATO Mokeke has signed an extension to his contract with Cape Town City which will see him staying at the club for another two years. The Citizens announced the news about Mokeke’s deal on Twitter yesterday. Mokeke said he’s happy to have signed a new contract with the team because they have been taking care of him. ?? | The club is delighted to announce that Thato Mokeke has signed a new deal which will see his existing contract extended by a further 2 years.Congratulations Keke! ??#iamCityFC pic.twitter.com/BF9IHaaub4  “The team has been looking after me for a while. I am very grateful for the opportunity they’ve given me,” he said. He added he’s happy to stay and is hopeful he can continue to help the team. Mokeke returned to City in 2019 after spending a few months with Chippa United who acquired his services while he was a free agent. The defender was part of the City’s side which beat Supersport United 2-1 in the 2016 Telkom Knockout final at Peter Mokaba Stadium. ?? Where he belongs...Thato Mokeke is here to stay ?? pic.twitter.com/GA3xzvTgez 